air game. If you have only one camp and someone tries to muscle in on it, I do not agree with that what so ever. That person should just be patient and wait their turn.   <br>
<br>
Now, I myself only quad Wyverns at this time. It is funny how there are camps for the Othmirs, but not the Wyverns. No big deal as far as I'm concerned, but I've run into some players that will call the SS tower with the Wyverns as a camp. I pulled from there once before, and got a angry tell saying &quot;Hey, I'm camping these!&quot; I replied that I had never heard of a camp for the Wyverns (which I never had at the time) but thought it over. It was a Monk or Druid I think. The tower did have a group of Wyverns all together, and I agreed with him that it was his camp and that I would not pull from there anymore, even though others might not of seen it that way. I just thought it was the polite thing to do. <br>
<br>
I guess the main thing here is be polite and treat others how you would like to be treated. It can be very frustrating trying to get a camp or mobs, but sooner or later you will if you have a little patience <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Also, you might make some new friends while you are waiting for your &quot;camp&quot;<br>
